<p itemprop="description">Incident management involves responding to, managing, and resolving unplanned interruptions or reductions in quality of IT services to restore normal service operations as quickly as possible.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the importance of incident management and recognise common incident types and response procedures in government IT services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can respond to incidents following established procedures, escalate appropriately, and contribute to incident resolution activities.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can manage complex incidents, coordinate response teams, conduct post-incident reviews, and improve incident management processes.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can design enterprise incident management frameworks, lead major incident responses, and drive continuous improvement in service resilience.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

